Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Founded in 1929, NAREE is a non profit association of real estate writers, editors, columnists, authors and communicators more than 600 members nationwide. The association meets in different US cities three times per year. In the Winter, NAREE members gather for a Design Trends Snapshot and Networking Reception usually during the National Association of Home Builders "International Builders Show." In the late Spring/early Summer, members meet for NAREE's Annual Spring Conference. NAREE leaders put together panels of newsmakers and trend setters to discuss issues of the day and to answer reporter questions on breaking stories. Professional development sessions and/or area tours are also scheduled. NAREE's Annual Real Estate Journalism Conference includes NAREE University peer-to-peer journalism workshops and "NAREE's Meet the Press," a one-on-one opportunity for freelance writers, columnists, and publicists to take part in a mini press tour -- visiting with up to a dozen of the nation's leading real estate journalists gathered under one roof. The association also presents awards to the winners of the Annual Real Estate Journalism Competition and the Bruss Book Competition.

Description: High quality and healthy foods are in high demand.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: THE PROBLEM  High quality and healthy foods are in high demand. Everyday discerning shoppers are wanting to supplement their normal grocery purchases with top-quality local products. For that demand there are only a few options and none of them are ideal for most consumers. The consumer must try to find time in their busy schedule to travel to a farmers market. Consumers can shop at a high end grocery store like Whole Foods where the quality is good but most products still aren't coming from local sources. There are other local options available like CSA boxes but they do not combine choice, quality, and convenience.    THE SOLUTION  The Find Veggies solution is connecting busy consumers with locally made, quality products. Consumers can shop, check out, and have them delivered. Very simple and convenient for their active busy lives.    Our solution helps the farmers market vendors. Currently vendors and farmers have limited ways to get the word out about what products they have for sale. They are busy creating or growing their products all week and don't have time or knowledge to market their goods. Find Veggies will act as the marketing arm for the vendors by driving more customers to them and increasing sales.    THE COMPETITION  We know there are others in the fresh vegetable business. Many high end retailers like Whole Foods and Spouts. Many cities have CSA boxes however these do not allow you to pick what you want and when you want them. Some startups have tried to solve the farm to phone problem but Find Veggies approach is different. We are not replicating warehouses or grocery stores. We simply extend the sales beyond the farmers market stall.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Food and Beverage, Mobile, Software

Description: Mentr is a platform that connects people with a desire to learn different skills or trades with those that have mastered them.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Mentr's mission is to create an online and mobile platform that connects people with a desire to learn different skills or trades with those that have mastered them. The theory being - the ultimate shortcut to success in anything in life or career is mentorship. We believe everyone has the ability to teach something valuable and that people in general have an inherent love of learning.  Mentr is designed to combine the fun, social networking aspects of apps like Bumble and Shapr, with learning platforms like Udemy, Upwork, and Skillshare. The core concept surrounds the notion that apps already exist allowing people to monetize their tangible assets (like Turo, Uber, Airbnb, etc), but there aren't many platforms that give people the ability to monetize their intangible assets like skills/knowledge/experience. Udemy and Masterclass are tremendous forums, however, 90% of people nearly never finish those courses much like don't online classes. We are committed to building an ecosystem for mentors and mentees to connect in a fun, meaningful, and rewarding way.

Description: A truly radical, magical way to motivate kids to learn.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Hiperware's app is a clever way to motivate kids to learn and practice reading or math every day.  For most kids, no math or reading app can be more interesting to use regularly when compared with Netflix or the latest game. This translates into a parenting dilemma, now that 2 out of 3 American kids use tablets. Without regular use or practice, educational apps bear little benefit. With the Learn & Earn app, parents motivate kids by connecting learning goals to actual rewards. E.g, parents may set a goal that says "If my child does 10 mins of math for 20 days, I'm willing to spend $10 in rewards." Kids start off by choosing one of 100s of rewards to earn. Once they meet their goal, the app helps initiate purchase via Amazon.com or iTunes, so kids receive the reward at their doorstep. The app is available for US Grades 1-4 math, covering 100s of skills and a 500,000+ questionnaire. The app helps improve math, instill regular learning & make kids appreciate earning their own rewards.
